  "notes": "Karachay-Balkar (къарачай-малкъар), Kipchak Turkic of the North Caucasus, written in Cyrillic since 1937. Digraphs: <гъ> = /ʁ/, <къ> = /q/, <нг> = /ŋ/, <дж> = /dʒ/ (Karachay; the Balkar varieties have /ʒ/ or /z/ here). Front-rounded vowels are written with the Russian iotated letters: <ю> = /y/, <ё> = /ø/; <ы> = /ɯ/, <я> = /æ/ or /ja/. The soft/hard signs are orthographic only and are not mapped. Vowel harmony is not represented in the spelling.",
